{
  "text": "where q is a (generic) hidden state assignment for the observed tree x. The upward-downward algorithm, on the other hand, is an extension to trees of the Forward-Backward inference algorithm for HMMs on sequences [CITATION_1] which allows to compute the posterior of the hidden state variables given the observed tree x, i.e.,",
